  <widget type="label" version="2.0.0">
    <name>Label_6</name>
    <y>351</y>
    <width>481</width>
    <height>260</height>
    <text>In the display editor, the "Properties" panel will
show each property with a name like "Text" or "Foreground Color",
and a user interface for setting the value of that property.
For "Text", you can enter the text,
and for "Foreground Color" you can select the color from a dialog.

The property name shown in the editor can be localized,
i.e. translated into different languages.
Each property also has an internal name that is not localized
because it uniquely identifies the property in the display file and also
when accessed by Rules or Scripts.
That internal name is typically based on the English property name,
but all lowercase with underscores instead of spaces.
The internal name for "Foreground Color" is "foreground_color". </text>
  </widget>
  <widget type="label" version="2.0.0">
