  <widget type="label" version="2.0.0">
    <name>Label_8</name>
    <y>651</y>
    <width>541</width>
    <height>180</height>
    <text>Some widgets contain properties that are arrays and/or structures.

For example, the Multi-State LED has a "states" property that is an array.
The elements of the array are in turn strucures with a "value" and "color".

For access from Rules or Scripts these properties can be accessed via names
   "states[0].value",
   "states[1].color",
and so on.</text>
  </widget>
